cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a neural network architecture for predicting and imitating the behavior of a swarm of agents, which is relevant to the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses modifications to previous models for interaction systems, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The extension of the model to deal with uncertain environments is also relevant to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of artificial motion data suggests a potential application in computer vision (cs.CV).
